The three Zimbabwean nationals accused of murdering and assaulting two couples in Rhodes Park will only know their fate in March next year.The case was postponed in the Palm Ridge High Court to March 27 next year. Judge Papi Masopa said he needed time to consider his judgement. The evidence is lengthy, it needs time. I can t make a judgment on the remaining two days of the term, Masopa said.Admore Ndlovu, 23, Thabo Nkala, 25, and Mduduzi Mathibela Lawrence, 32, are accused of being part of a gang that attacked two couples and raped one of the women in October last year in Kensington. They are facing charges of robbery with aggravating circumstances, rape and murder. They have pleaded not guilty.They allegedly forced the women s husbands, Zukisa Khela and Sizwe Tyeke, to strip before forcing them into the lake where they drowned.Earlier Nkala and Ndlovu claimed Lawrence and a man called Cosmo stayed behind and committed the rapes. The charge sheet says the group armed with a gun and a knife forced their victims to lie on the ground. They used a knife to cut off the panties of both women and then allegedly raped them. They forced their partners to undress and pushed them into the lake where they drowned. The gang stole their clothes, jewellery and cellphones.During closing arguments, state prosecutor Monde Mbaqa told the court that each one of the accused should be found guilty of murder and rape because they acted together.Mbaqa said CCTV footage used by police officers had identified the suspects and played a crucial role in the case.NONDUMISO ZWANEnondumisoz@thenwage.co.za